Several persons have been confirmed killed in a fresh attack in Tamgborong Village, Riyom Local Government of Plateau State by gunmen suspected to be Fulani herdsmen. New Telegraph also gathered that attackers burnt down the entire village and farms products. President of Irigwe Youth Movement, Mr Chinge Dodo, confirmed the attack and said already the community has discovered five corpses as rescue and search operation is still ongoing. “Suspected Fulani herdsmen on Monday 17th June attacked Tamgborong, a community inhabited by IRIGWE people in Riyom Local Government have burnt down the entire village at the moment we have discovered five corpses as search and rescue operation is still on ongoing”. According to another source said the attack took place between 11 am and 12:00 noon on Monday by alleged Fulani herdsmen who invaded the village of Tamgborong shooting sporadically, destroying crops and burning houses. The Platea State Police Command Public Relation officer DSP Tyopev Mathias when contacted promised to issue a press statement as at the time of filing this report. <img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/9791c904-38a3-4418-b312-f92837c7a0b9.jpg?resize=576%2C960&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="576" height="960" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-219972" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/9791c904-38a3-4418-b312-f92837c7a0b9.jpg?w=576&amp;ssl=1 576w, https://i1.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/9791c904-38a3-4418-b312-f92837c7a0b9.jpg?resize=180%2C300&amp;ssl=1 180w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" data-recalc-dims="1"> <img src="https://i2.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/9650634d-d7a5-48ef-b086-8edb0c0b6663.jpg?resize=712%2C427&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="712" height="427" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-219973" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.newtelegraphng.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/9650634d-d7a5-48ef-b086-8edb0c0b6663.jpg?